# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
debug/
target/

# Engine sidecar binaries — staged during release builds by CI or by
# scripts/preflight-desktop-release.sh. They are rebuilt from the
# workspace crates every run and should never be committed.
desktop/src-tauri/binaries/

# Throwaway discovery spikes (Phase B of p5-hardening-and-t6-preflight).
# Anything under scratch/ is experimental and must not ship.
scratch/

# Universal-fidelity sprint measurement artefacts. These are produced
# by `graphengine-parsing parse` + `ge-analyze` on throwaway fixtures;
# the numbers live in the design-doc addenda and FOLLOWUPS.md, the
# raw .db/.json outputs are reproducible with the commands noted in
# the docs. Do not track them — they churn on every re-measurement.
experiments/results/gate*/
experiments/results/uf-*/
# Jorje-LSP / other ad-hoc instrumentation traces — reproducible by
# re-running the instrumentation commands logged in the corresponding
# docs (e.g. VALIDATION_RESULTS.md §"P0 timeboxed investigation"),
# and typically tens of MB; keep out of git, keep the analysis in md.
experiments/results/**/trace.jsonl

# Remove Cargo.lock from gitignore if creating an executable, leave it for libraries
# More information here https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/guide/cargo-toml-vs-cargo-lock.html
# Cargo.lock

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

