*.tmp
*.temp

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS filesystem metadata (DO NOT COMMIT)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local databases / runtime artifacts (DO NOT COMMIT)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SQLite / Memgraph sidecar artifacts created during parsing, tests, and local runs.
# These are non-deterministic binaries and create noisy diffs.
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite-shm
*.sqlite-wal

# NOTE: the rev-6.1 NPSP byte-identical regression-gate fixture
# (`experiments/results/NPSP/rev6.1/{parse.ab.sqlite,baseline.json,ab_report.json}`
# plus the top-level symlinks) is NOT tracked. It lives as a sha-pinned
# GitHub release asset (`regression-fixtures-2026-05-19`, key
# `rev6_1_regression_fixture` in experiments/artifacts.lock) and is
# fetched on demand by `scripts/setup.sh fixtures`. The `*.sqlite` and
# `*.json` paths under rev6.1/ are covered by the global rules above
# and the explicit block below; they are listed here to make the
# externalization policy obvious to future readers.
experiments/results/NPSP/rev6.1/
experiments/results/NPSP/parse.ab.sqlite
experiments/results/NPSP/baseline.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Runtime state (UF-FU-014)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Runtime SQLite databases written by gridseak binaries during a session
# show up in T7 git-signal hotspots as co-changing with source. Global
# `*.db{,-wal,-shm}` above already matches these, but the documentation
# anchor for UF-FU-014 remains: runtime state is not source activity and
# must never be tracked.

# Calibration: cloned repos (large, re-cloneable) and transient artifacts
graphengine-analysis/calibration/repos/
graphengine-analysis/calibration/.env

